                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="10" value="for dimensions: dictionary scoring based on frequency (frequency of keywords within a dimension divided by all words within the relevant segment). In the case of intensity I could do: score= moderate intensity + (2*high intensity) / total words" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="480" y="90" width="120" height="200" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="11" value="verifying if dictionary scoring is actually efficient on a small sample (1 random press release segment per year per actor)" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="620" y="90" width="120" height="310" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="12" value="scaling to the rest of the datset! Now every press release has a rhetorical positioning vector." style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="760" y="90" width="120" height="310" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="13" value="To compute divergence: distance between the vectors of two press releases (i.e. France/EEAS, or Germany/EEAS) from a very similar timeframe. To compute divergence before and after coordination event (EU council meeting where Russia was discussed), looking at press releases 2 weeks before and after the event. HERE: I am thinking of using either Euclidean distance, or sum of differences. They both have pluses and minuses." style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="900" y="90" width="160" height="310" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="14" value="a validation/ further source of insights measure: cosine similarity. I have found cosine similarity to be quite popular in literature, and I think it could give me further insights about the text, and how it corresponds with my other measure.&amp;nbsp;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1080" y="90" width="160" height="310" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
