                <mxCell id="18" value="main ideas:&lt;div&gt;- rhetorical positioning as proxy for foreign policy stance&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- rhetorical positioning has 4 dimensions (plus issue distribution) and is presented as a vector of the scores for those dimensions&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- score computed as frequency of dimension keywords divided by all words in the text&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- divergence computed as distance between two vectors (i.e. EEAS and France within a time frame)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- secondary check: cosine similarity (so divergence could be 1- cosine similarity result); this would give further insights.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Below process presented in detail:&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
